ivardefs.name: notConsumed
ivardefs.desc: Indicator when a patient is in a setting where it is helpful to know if food was not consumed, such as it was refused, held (as in tube feedings), or otherwise not provided. If a consumption is being recorded from an app, such as MyFitnessPal, this indica

ivardefs.name: notConsumedReason
ivardefs.desc: Document the reason the food or fluid was not consumed, such as refused, held, etc.

ivardefs.name: nutritionProduct
ivardefs.desc: Identifies the food or fluid product that was consumed. This is potentially a link to a resource representing the details of the food product (TBD) or a simple attribute carrying a code that identifies the food from a known list of foods.

ivardefs.name: rate
ivardefs.desc: Rate at which enteral feeding was administered.

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: Indicates what a category of item that was consumed: eg., food, fluid, enteral, etc.

properties.desc: What food or fluid product or item was consumed.
